columns.text:
Because the periodic payment is monthly and the stated rate of 5.2% is an annual rate, we'll divide the rate by 12 to get the monthly rate we'll use to determine the monthly payment.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &=\dfrac{0.052}{12}
\\[10pt]
&= {0.43\%}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, we'll consider the rate of 0.43%.
